WEBVTT

00:09.810 --> 00:11.245
- * ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR

00:11.279 --> 00:13.214
* ONE, TWO, THREE,
FOUR, FIVE, SIX *

00:13.247 --> 00:14.448
* SHAKE IT, DUDE

00:14.482 --> 00:22.423
*

00:28.429 --> 00:29.763
* ONE, TWO, DO IT

00:29.797 --> 00:32.133
*

00:32.166 --> 00:33.501
* ONE, TWO, THREE

00:33.534 --> 00:35.369
- * FOUR, FOUR

00:35.403 --> 00:38.172
*

00:40.174 --> 00:42.143
- EDDIE, YOU WANT TO PASS
THESE OUT TO THE GUYS THERE?

00:42.176 --> 00:44.845
- SURE.
- THANKS.

00:44.878 --> 00:47.181
NOW, THAT'S IT, PRISON CELL.
REALLY GIVE IT TO HIM.

00:47.215 --> 00:50.384
REMEMBER, HE'S IN FOR TEN YEARS
HARD LABOR.

00:50.418 --> 00:52.386
UH, GUYS
IN THE ELEVATOR?

00:52.420 --> 00:53.554
YEAH, DON'T LET
OUR MEMBERS DOWN.

00:53.587 --> 00:55.589
KEEP IT UP.

00:55.623 --> 00:57.225
MICHAEL, DON'T CROSS
IN FRONT OF CAMERA LIKE THAT.

00:57.258 --> 00:58.626
THANKS.
- [chuckles]

00:58.659 --> 01:01.695
- MEN ON THE ORAL REEF?
SPLASH DOWN.

01:01.729 --> 01:05.866
[men moaning]
EASY, MERMAN, EASY.

01:05.899 --> 01:09.170
KEEP IT LIQUID.

01:09.203 --> 01:12.206
THAT'S IT.

01:12.240 --> 01:14.542
[bubbles pop]

01:14.575 --> 01:16.177
- MIND IF I ASK YOU
A QUESTION, TED?

01:16.210 --> 01:18.446
- SHOOT.
- OH, YEAH!

01:18.479 --> 01:20.314
- NOT YOU.
- [groans]

01:20.348 --> 01:22.416
- SORRY, TED.
- YOU.

01:22.450 --> 01:23.484
- HOW DO YOU GET
ANY WORK DONE

01:23.517 --> 01:26.320
WITH ALL THESE HOT
AND HORNY GUYS SURROUNDING YOU?

01:26.354 --> 01:28.522
- YEAH, IF IT WERE ME,
I'D HAVE A PERMANENT BONER.

01:28.556 --> 01:30.424
- THOUGHT YOU ALREADY DID.

01:30.458 --> 01:32.460
- HOT AND HORNY ACTION
IS MY WORK.

01:32.493 --> 01:33.861
AH.

01:33.894 --> 01:35.396
IT'S LIKE
A DREAM COME TRUE.

01:35.429 --> 01:37.498
- I CAN GUESS
WHAT KIND OF DREAM.

01:37.531 --> 01:40.201
- WHOEVER THOUGHT THAT YOU,
THEODORE SCHMIDT,

01:40.234 --> 01:43.137
LOSER, REJECT, PUTZ,
WOULD WIND UP

01:43.171 --> 01:44.872
BEING THE LUCKIEST FUCKER
IN THE WORLD?

01:44.905 --> 01:47.208
- DO I DETECT A NOTE
OF ENVY, BRI?

01:47.241 --> 01:48.476
- HMM.

01:48.509 --> 01:52.346
- [chuckles]
- I GOTTA GET BACK TO WORK.

01:52.380 --> 01:53.847
I HAVE A NEW ACCOUNT--

01:53.881 --> 01:55.483
BABY WIPES.

01:55.516 --> 01:56.784
- YEAH, I GOTTA GO.
- EW.

01:56.817 --> 01:59.220
- COMIC BOOKS I GOTTA UNPACK
AND FILE AND DISPLAY

01:59.253 --> 02:00.421
AND UNPACK AND FILE
AND DISPLAY--

02:00.454 --> 02:01.455
- MR. SCHMIDT.
- [groans]

02:01.489 --> 02:02.490
- AS FOR ME...
- HERE YOU ARE.

02:02.523 --> 02:04.492
- THANK YOU, EDDIE.

02:04.525 --> 02:06.527
I'VE GOT,
UH, LET'S SEE,

02:06.560 --> 02:09.297
RIM-O-RAMA FROM 2:00 TO 5:00.

02:09.330 --> 02:12.800
I'VE GOT DILDO DAZE,
SPELLED D-A-Z-E--

02:12.833 --> 02:14.668
ISN'T THAT CUTE?
[chuckles]

02:14.702 --> 02:16.270
FROM 6:00 TO 9:00.

02:16.304 --> 02:17.838
- THANKS FOR NOT RUBBING
OUR NOSES IN IT.

02:17.871 --> 02:20.274
- AW, YOU'RE WELCOME.

02:20.308 --> 02:21.675
I'D ASK YOU BOYS TO STAY,

02:21.709 --> 02:23.777
BUT I KNOW YOU NEED
TO TODDLE ON BACK

02:23.811 --> 02:28.516
TO YOUR LACKLUSTER
LITTLE LIVES.

02:28.549 --> 02:29.550
- TRY NOT TO WORK
TOO HARD.

02:29.583 --> 02:33.854
- FUCKER.
- [chuckles]

02:33.887 --> 02:35.423
[sighs]

02:36.824 --> 02:41.195
- YOU KNOW YOU MAKE LOVE
LIKE YOU PLAY YOUR VIOLIN?

02:41.229 --> 02:44.598
- WITH AN ACCOMPANIST IN FRONT
OF A CHEERING AUDIENCE?

02:44.632 --> 02:45.833
ON THE STREET CORNER
FOR CASH?

02:45.866 --> 02:47.768
- [laughs]

02:47.801 --> 02:51.272
LIKE YOU'RE
IN A TRANCE.

02:51.305 --> 02:52.673
WITH YOUR EYES CLOSED.

02:52.706 --> 02:55.209
- AND YOU'RE MY INSTRUMENT.

02:55.243 --> 02:57.645
- [chuckles]

02:57.678 --> 03:01.282
- FIRST, I TUNE YOU...
- [snorts]

03:01.315 --> 03:04.685
- AND THEN, I STROKE YOU
WITH MY BOW...

03:04.718 --> 03:08.556
- [chuckles]

03:08.589 --> 03:11.559
- AND THEN I MAKE BEAUTIFUL
SOUNDS POUR OUT OF YOU.

03:11.592 --> 03:12.960
- [sighs]

03:12.993 --> 03:15.963
- MWAH.

03:18.599 --> 03:21.569
- [sighs]

03:24.938 --> 03:29.243
I HAVE TO GO.

03:34.515 --> 03:37.518
- YOU HAVE BIG PLANS TONIGHT?
- OH, YEAH.

03:37.551 --> 03:39.353
A DATE WITH COPYBOY.

03:39.387 --> 03:41.355
I'M RUNNING OFF POSTERS
FOR MY COMIC BOOK.

03:41.389 --> 03:43.591
- AW, THAT'S AWESOME.

03:43.624 --> 03:44.858
- WE'RE GOING TO PLASTER
LIBERTY AVENUE,

03:44.892 --> 03:46.260
TRY TO SELL
SOME OF IT.

03:46.294 --> 03:47.461
- WELL, MAYBE WE COULD
WORK TOGETHER.

03:47.495 --> 03:49.330
I FIDDLE,
YOU PEDDLE?

03:49.363 --> 03:51.532
STARVING ARTISTS, INC.
- [laughs]

03:51.565 --> 03:54.268
THAT'S US.

03:54.302 --> 03:56.236
[rips Velcro]

04:06.747 --> 04:09.817
- YOU KNOW,
IF YOU STAYED SOMETIME,

04:09.850 --> 04:12.320
WE COULD
WAKE UP TOGETHER,

04:12.353 --> 04:14.021
WATCH THE SUN RISE.

04:14.054 --> 04:17.991
MAKES EVERYTHING
RED AND GOLD.

04:24.732 --> 04:27.668
[indistinct chatter]

04:27.701 --> 04:28.702
[pins clatter]
- YES!

04:28.736 --> 04:30.338
- [cheers]

04:30.371 --> 04:33.073
YOU ARE SO GOOD.

04:33.106 --> 04:34.775
- HEY.

04:34.808 --> 04:37.778
HOW COME WHEN I GOT A STRIKE,
I DIDN'T GET ONE OF THOSE?

04:37.811 --> 04:38.646
- HEY, DONNA.

04:38.679 --> 04:40.080
HOW COME WHEN HORVATH
GOT A STRIKE,

04:40.113 --> 04:41.349
HE DIDN'T GET ONE
OF THOSE?

04:41.382 --> 04:43.751
[both chuckle]

04:43.784 --> 04:45.519
- COME HERE.

04:45.553 --> 04:47.855
- OH, I'M UP.

04:47.888 --> 04:51.659
- * TENNESSEE,
MAKE A HOME FOR ME *

04:51.692 --> 04:52.926
- [laughs]
- NO.

04:52.960 --> 04:56.397
- LET'S GO, DEB.

04:56.430 --> 04:59.099
*

04:59.132 --> 05:03.704
- LOVE YOUR BALLS.
- THANKS.

05:04.738 --> 05:05.706
[pins clatter]

05:05.739 --> 05:07.375
- OH, MY GOD, YOU DID IT!

05:07.408 --> 05:10.544
YOU GOT A STRIKE!
IT WAS FANTASTIC!

05:10.578 --> 05:11.712
[excited chatter]

05:11.745 --> 05:13.814
- LET'S SEE.

05:13.847 --> 05:15.916
- YES! ALL RIGHT!

05:15.949 --> 05:17.918
LET'S HEAR IT FOR ME!

05:17.951 --> 05:22.055
- OH, I'M SO...
- OUR LADY OF THE LANES.

05:22.089 --> 05:27.561
- [laughing]

05:27.595 --> 05:28.762
- EXCUSE ME.

05:28.796 --> 05:30.831
BUT THERE HAPPEN
TO BE A LOT

05:30.864 --> 05:32.833
OF REALLY GREAT GAY BOWLERS.

05:32.866 --> 05:33.834
- NAME ONE.

05:33.867 --> 05:35.869
- I'LL NAME MORE THAN ONE.

05:35.903 --> 05:37.505
WE HAVE
OUR OWN GAY BOWLING TEAM

05:37.538 --> 05:39.440
RIGHT HERE IN PITTSBURGH...

05:39.473 --> 05:40.808
THE LIBERTY BALLS.

05:40.841 --> 05:42.042
AND THEY CAN KNOCK
THE FUCKING PINS

05:42.075 --> 05:43.043
OUT FROM UNDER YOU.

05:43.076 --> 05:45.379
- HEY, BRING 'EM ON.

05:45.413 --> 05:47.548
- COULD WE GET BACK
TO OUR GAME, PLEASE?

05:47.581 --> 05:49.783
- ANYTIME, ANYWHERE.

05:49.817 --> 05:51.952
- HOW ABOUT HERE,
FRIDAY NIGHT?

05:51.985 --> 05:53.721
- COPS AGAINST THE QUEERS.

05:53.754 --> 05:56.590
- FORGET IT,
IT'S A BAD IDEA.

05:56.624 --> 05:58.726
- AFRAID THEY'RE GONNA KICK
YOUR ASS?

05:58.759 --> 05:59.927
- TRUST ME,

05:59.960 --> 06:03.464
THEY WON'T BE ANYWHERE
NEAR MY ASS.

06:03.497 --> 06:06.900
COME ON.
WHO'S NEXT?

06:06.934 --> 06:09.470
[both moaning]

06:09.503 --> 06:10.771
- HOW COULD WE
HAVE BEEN AFRAID

06:10.804 --> 06:12.640
THAT IT WOULD NEVER
BE LIKE THIS AGAIN?

06:12.673 --> 06:14.408
- LEDA WAS RIGHT.

06:14.442 --> 06:16.009
ALL WE NEEDED WAS
A JUMP START.

06:16.043 --> 06:19.146
- SHE JUMPED US ALL RIGHT.

06:19.179 --> 06:21.081
- I'M GLAD WHAT HAPPENED
HAPPENED.

06:21.114 --> 06:22.550
- YOU ARE?

06:22.583 --> 06:24.652
- IT MADE ME REALIZE

06:24.685 --> 06:26.954
THAT DESPITE
OUR UPS AND DOWNS,

06:26.987 --> 06:29.757
AND THE OCCASIONAL DRY SPELL,

06:29.790 --> 06:32.593
YOU'RE STILL THE ONLY ONE
I EVER WANT TO BE WITH.

06:32.626 --> 06:36.797
- [sighs]
OH, MEL.

06:42.670 --> 06:44.071
- HEY, GIRLS.

06:44.104 --> 06:46.039
- [gasps]

06:46.073 --> 06:47.941
- LEDA?

06:47.975 --> 06:50.511
- HI.

06:50.544 --> 06:51.645
- I HEARD THE FLOORBOARDS

06:51.679 --> 06:53.080
SQUEAKING OVERHEAD AND--

06:53.113 --> 06:54.915
- OUR NEXT RENOVATION.

06:54.948 --> 06:57.918
- FIGURED,
SINCE YOU'RE UP,

06:57.951 --> 07:00.821
WHY DON'T WE HAVE
A LITTLE SLUMBER PARTY?

07:00.854 --> 07:03.824
JUST US GIRLS.

07:03.857 --> 07:07.895
[Gus crying
on baby monitor]

07:07.928 --> 07:10.498
- OH, GOSH.
THERE'S GUS.

07:10.531 --> 07:16.169
- I-I BETTER GO SEE
WHAT'S WRONG.

07:16.203 --> 07:18.772
[chuckles nervously]

07:18.806 --> 07:22.009
[Gus wailing]

07:22.042 --> 07:24.044
- THANKS
FOR A GOOD DAY'S JERK.

07:24.077 --> 07:27.147
HERE YOU GO, FOR YOU.

07:27.180 --> 07:30.484
THIS IS FOR YOU.

07:30.518 --> 07:33.554
ULYSSES...

07:33.587 --> 07:35.956
PERSEUS...

07:35.989 --> 07:40.127
HERCULES...

07:40.160 --> 07:42.663
STANLEY, THANKS
FOR A GOOD DAY'S JERK.

07:42.696 --> 07:44.164
[door closes]

07:44.197 --> 07:45.699
- I DON'T GET IT,
MR. SCHMIDT.

07:45.733 --> 07:47.100
- GET WHAT, EDDIE?

07:47.134 --> 07:49.236
- I OVERHEARD YOU
TELLING YOUR FRIENDS

07:49.269 --> 07:50.237
THAT IT WAS LIKE
A DREAM COME TRUE

07:50.270 --> 07:52.873
BEING HERE WITH
ALL THESE HOT AND HORNY GUYS.

07:52.906 --> 07:54.842
[water splashes]

07:54.875 --> 07:56.877
AND YET,

07:56.910 --> 07:59.947
JUST NOW
WHEN THEY ALL WALKED BY YOU,

07:59.980 --> 08:01.248
YOU BARELY LOOKED UP.

08:01.281 --> 08:03.917
- WELL, I WAS PASSING OUT
PAYCHECKS.

08:03.951 --> 08:05.919
YOU KNOW,
HAD TO MAKE SURE THE NAME

08:05.953 --> 08:07.054
WENT WITH THE DICK.

08:07.087 --> 08:09.657
[chuckles]

08:09.690 --> 08:12.025
- BUT WHAT ABOUT
THE OTHER NIGHT?

08:12.059 --> 08:13.026
- OTHER NIGHT?

08:13.060 --> 08:15.529
- DON'T YOU REMEMBER?

08:15.563 --> 08:17.865
DUELING DICKS?

08:17.898 --> 08:20.167
OVER 12 HOURS
OF NONSTOP J.O. ACTION?

08:20.200 --> 08:22.970
- OH, RIGHT.

08:23.003 --> 08:25.038
- IT HAD TO HAVE BEEN ONE OF
THE PORN EVENTS OF THE CENTURY,

08:25.072 --> 08:27.708
AND YET YOU JUST SAT THERE,
DOING YOUR BOOKS.

08:27.741 --> 08:30.277
YOU DIDN'T LOOK UP
THROUGH THE WHOLE THING.

08:30.310 --> 08:33.781
NOT ONCE.

08:33.814 --> 08:36.850
- WELL THAT'S--
THAT'S VERY OBSERVANT, EDDIE,

08:36.884 --> 08:39.887
BUT YOU HAVE TO UNDERSTAND,
THIS IS WORK.

08:39.920 --> 08:42.222
AND I'M THE BOSS.

08:42.255 --> 08:45.058
I HAVE A PROFESSIONAL DEMEANOR
I HAVE TO MAINTAIN.

08:45.092 --> 08:47.127
HOWEVER...
[chuckles]

08:47.160 --> 08:50.698
IT DOESN'T MEAN I WASN'T LOVING
EVERY MINUTE OF IT.

08:55.869 --> 08:57.638
- WELL,

08:57.671 --> 08:59.039
IF YOU DON'T NEED ME
FOR ANYTHING ELSE,

08:59.072 --> 09:00.273
DO YOU MIND IF I TAKE OFF?

09:00.307 --> 09:03.310
- OH, NO, YOU GO AHEAD.
I'LL LOCK UP.

09:03.343 --> 09:07.681
- THANKS, MR. SCHMIDT.

09:07.715 --> 09:08.682
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

09:08.716 --> 09:10.283
- YEAH.

09:10.317 --> 09:13.621
[door opens, closes]

09:20.093 --> 09:24.197
[tapping keys]

09:24.231 --> 09:27.200
[men moaning on video]

09:50.323 --> 09:52.259
[video stops]

10:03.370 --> 10:06.306
[door slides]

10:09.342 --> 10:11.011
- YOU'RE WORKING LATE.

10:11.044 --> 10:14.314
- WELL, THAT'S ONE OF
THE BENEFITS OF BEING A PARTNER.

10:14.347 --> 10:16.717
YOU GIVE SOMEONE SOMETHING
TO DO, THEY FUCK IT UP,

10:16.750 --> 10:18.852
AND THEN YOU GET
TO DO IT YOURSELF.

10:18.886 --> 10:20.854
- YOU ASKED FOR IT.

10:20.888 --> 10:23.390
- YEAH, AND I GOT IT.

10:23.423 --> 10:25.258
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

10:25.292 --> 10:26.694
- STUDYING.

10:26.727 --> 10:28.361
AND I HAD TO GET THESE.

10:28.395 --> 10:30.998
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

10:31.031 --> 10:33.366
- MY OWN LITTLE
ADVERTISING GENIUS.

10:33.400 --> 10:35.135
- [chuckles]

10:35.168 --> 10:37.170
- I TOLD YOU
I'D HELP YOU.

10:37.204 --> 10:39.139
- YOU'RE TOO BUSY.

10:39.172 --> 10:41.341
- COME HERE.
- MM.

10:41.374 --> 10:44.778
I HAVE TO SHOWER.
I STINK.

10:47.014 --> 10:50.217
- FROM STUDYING?
- [chuckles]

10:50.250 --> 10:53.320
SWEATING OVER A PROJECT.

10:55.022 --> 10:57.991
[Blackout plays]

10:58.025 --> 11:04.197
*

11:04.231 --> 11:06.767
YOU SCARED ME.

11:06.800 --> 11:08.401
- RELAX.

11:08.435 --> 11:10.871
IT'S NOT THAT KIND
OF A SHOWER SCENE.

11:10.904 --> 11:16.176
*

11:16.209 --> 11:18.211
- I THOUGHT YOU HAD WORK
TO DO.

11:18.245 --> 11:20.914
- BUT I GOT
ALL SWEATY TOO.

11:20.948 --> 11:23.851
*

11:23.884 --> 11:26.186
- * THE POWER GRID
IS DOWN *

11:26.219 --> 11:28.055
* MELTED WIRES

11:28.088 --> 11:30.323
* AND CIRCUITS BLOWN
- BRIAN?

11:30.357 --> 11:33.160
- * CAN'T DO IT
ON MY OWN *

11:33.193 --> 11:37.130
* DON'T LEAVE ME ALONE

11:37.164 --> 11:41.068
* EVEN WHEN THE TRUTH
WILL CUT *

11:41.101 --> 11:44.872
* SO DEEPLY TO THE BONE

11:44.905 --> 11:47.474
* CAN'T DO IT
ON MY OWN *

11:47.507 --> 11:50.210
* DON'T LEAVE ME ALONE

11:50.243 --> 11:52.345
- [sighs]

11:52.379 --> 11:54.782
- * ALL OF MY OBSESSIONS

11:54.815 --> 11:59.519
* AREN'T ENOUGH
WHEN I'M ALONE *

11:59.552 --> 12:02.222
* CAN'T DO IT ON MY OWN

12:02.255 --> 12:07.227
* DON'T LEAVE ME ALONE

12:07.260 --> 12:10.197
* WANDERING IN THIS WORLD

12:10.230 --> 12:14.034
* WITH NO DIRECTION HOME

12:14.067 --> 12:16.503
* CAN'T DO IT
ON MY OWN *

12:16.536 --> 12:21.208
* DON'T LEAVE ME ALONE

12:21.241 --> 12:24.311
* TIME

12:24.344 --> 12:28.916
* CHANGES EVERYTHING

12:28.949 --> 12:31.418
* TIME

12:31.451 --> 12:35.522
* CHANGES EVERYTHING

12:35.555 --> 12:38.258
* IT'S TIME

12:38.291 --> 12:40.493
- THANK GOD
HE STARTED CRYING.

12:40.527 --> 12:41.795
- I'VE NEVER BEEN SO HAPPY

12:41.829 --> 12:42.863
TO HEAR HIM SCREAM
HIS LUNGS OUT.

12:42.896 --> 12:43.997
- I MEAN,
UNFORTUNATELY,

12:44.031 --> 12:44.965
WE CAN'T COUNT ON HIM
TO SAVE US

12:44.998 --> 12:48.001
NEXT TIME SHE SHOWS UP
WANTING TO DIVE IN.

12:48.035 --> 12:50.070
- WE COULD ALWAYS PUT
A LOCK ON THE BEDROOM DOOR.

12:50.103 --> 12:51.571
- [laughs]
- I'M SERIOUS.

12:51.604 --> 12:53.573
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE TO SET UP
SOME SORT OF BLOCKADE.

12:53.606 --> 12:55.475
- WELL, THE PROBLEM IS
SHE DOESN'T SEEM TO REALIZE

12:55.508 --> 12:56.910
IT WAS A ONE-TIME THING.

12:56.944 --> 12:57.911
- HOW COULD SHE NOT?

12:57.945 --> 12:59.813
IT WAS JUST A SPONTANEOUS,

12:59.847 --> 13:01.381
"I DON'T KNOW
HOW THE HELL IT HAPPENED,

13:01.414 --> 13:03.416
BUT THERE YOU ARE, DOING IT"
SORT OF THING.

13:03.450 --> 13:05.252
- WELL, WE JUST NEED
TO BE HONEST WITH HER.

13:05.285 --> 13:06.954
- OKAY.

13:06.987 --> 13:07.988
YOU DO IT.

13:08.021 --> 13:09.322
- ME?
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

13:09.356 --> 13:11.158
YOU WERE THERE TOO.
- I KNOW.

13:11.191 --> 13:12.192
BUT YOU'RE MUCH BETTER

13:12.225 --> 13:13.193
AT REJECTING PEOPLE
THAN I AM.

13:13.226 --> 13:14.194
- EXCUSE ME?

13:14.227 --> 13:16.897
- I MEANT THAT
IN THE HIGHEST FORM OF PRAISE.

13:16.930 --> 13:17.730
I MEAN, YOU'RE GREAT

13:17.764 --> 13:19.099
WHEN IT COMES
TO FIRING THE SITTER

13:19.132 --> 13:20.901
OR SAYING NO
TO PHONE SOLICITORS.

13:20.934 --> 13:22.435
I MEAN, HOW MANY TIMES
HAVE YOU TOLD YOUR MOTHER

13:22.469 --> 13:23.570
SHE CAN'T COME LIVE
WITH US?

13:23.603 --> 13:25.038
- OH, SO IN OTHER WORDS,

13:25.072 --> 13:26.573
YOU'RE A TIMID LITTLE SHIKSA.
- THAT'S ME.

13:26.606 --> 13:28.208
- WELL, THIS IS
A LOT MORE DIFFICULT

13:28.241 --> 13:30.277
THAN TELLING THE SALVATION ARMY
TO TAKE A HIKE.

13:30.310 --> 13:31.244
LEDA'S A DEAR FRIEND.

13:31.278 --> 13:34.081
NOT ONLY THAT,
SHE'S DOING US A BIG FAVOR.

13:34.114 --> 13:35.548
- WAIT, THAT'S IT.

13:35.582 --> 13:37.550
THE DEAL WAS,
SHE COULD COME STAY WITH US

13:37.584 --> 13:39.352
WHILE SHE WAS WORKING
ON THE STUDIO, RIGHT?

13:39.386 --> 13:41.321
- RIGHT.

13:41.354 --> 13:44.925
- THE STUDIO'S
PRACTICALLY DONE.

13:44.958 --> 13:47.560
SO WE DON'T SAY ANYTHING,
AND IN A COUPLE OF DAYS--

13:47.594 --> 13:49.863
- OUR PROBLEM MOVES OUT
WITH HER?

13:49.897 --> 13:52.032
- YES.
PLEASE.

13:52.065 --> 13:54.001
- [sighs]

13:56.603 --> 13:59.572
[violin music]

13:59.606 --> 14:07.614
*

14:12.585 --> 14:15.588
- WE'LL POSTER GAYOPOLIS
A LOT FASTER IF WE SPLIT UP.

14:15.622 --> 14:17.190
I'LL GET THE OTHER SIDE
OF THE STREET.

14:17.224 --> 14:19.459
- GOOD IDEA.
- OKAY.

14:19.492 --> 14:27.434
*

14:32.672 --> 14:34.607
HEY, HOW'S IT GOING?

14:34.641 --> 14:36.643
- WELL, BUSINESS
IS A LITTLE SLOW,

14:36.676 --> 14:39.112
BUT AT LEAST
ONE DEVOTED FAN IS HERE.

14:39.146 --> 14:40.113
- THANKS.

14:40.147 --> 14:43.550
- NOT YOU.
BERTHA.

14:43.583 --> 14:45.452
SHE NEVER MISSES
A PERFORMANCE.

14:45.485 --> 14:47.254
- [chuckles]

14:47.287 --> 14:49.122
- WHAT HAVE YOU GOT THERE?

14:49.156 --> 14:50.023
- POSTERS.

14:50.057 --> 14:53.994
- AH, FOR YOUR COMIC BOOK.
RAGE.

14:54.027 --> 14:56.663
- I'M HOPING TO SELL ENOUGH
TO PAY FOR TUITION NEXT YEAR.

14:56.696 --> 14:57.697
- WELL, YOU NEVER KNOW.

14:57.730 --> 14:58.698
I HEAR THE GUYS
WHO DID X-MEN

14:58.731 --> 15:00.200
MADE A FORTUNE.
- YEAH?

15:00.233 --> 15:03.303
- HEY, YOU WANT TO GO
GET A LATTE?

15:03.336 --> 15:04.671
- I CAN'T,
I HAVE TO PUT THESE UP.

15:04.704 --> 15:06.539
- HUH.

15:06.573 --> 15:08.541
OKAY, WELL, MAYBE THIS WEEKEND
WE CAN GO SEE A MOVIE.

15:08.575 --> 15:10.577
YOU LIKE FRENCH FILMS?

15:10.610 --> 15:12.245
- I'VE NEVER BEEN TO ONE.

15:12.279 --> 15:15.148
- NEVER BEEN?
PEASANT.

15:15.182 --> 15:18.051
THE STUDENT FILM SOCIETY IS
HAVING A TRUFFAUT RETROSPECTIVE.

15:18.085 --> 15:20.053
THEY'RE SHOWING JULES ET JIM,

15:20.087 --> 15:23.056
A STORY ABOUT TWO MEN IN LOVE
WITH THE SAME WOMAN.

15:23.090 --> 15:25.725
ONLY IF YOU'LL NOTICE,
HER NAME'S NOT IN THE TITLE,

15:25.758 --> 15:27.060
WHICH LEADS ME TO BELIEVE

15:27.094 --> 15:29.196
THAT THEY'RE IN LOVE
WITH EACH OTHER.

15:29.229 --> 15:32.265
- IT'S HARD ENOUGH
LOVING ONE PERSON.

15:32.299 --> 15:34.334
- BUT IF YOU'RE THE ONE
THE OTHER TWO ARE IN LOVE WITH,

15:34.367 --> 15:37.704
THEN YOU CAN BREAK
BOTH THEIR HEARTS.

15:52.385 --> 15:53.486
- I'LL CALL YOU
ABOUT THE WEEKEND.

15:53.520 --> 15:55.022
- SURE.
THAT'S COOL.

15:55.055 --> 16:00.127
- JULES ET JIM
OR SOMETHING.

16:00.160 --> 16:03.363
[indistinct chatter]

16:03.396 --> 16:05.365
[laughter in background]

16:07.467 --> 16:09.736
- HEY, PORN KING, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE AMID THE SERFS?

16:09.769 --> 16:11.571
- FUCK OFF.

16:11.604 --> 16:13.306
- NOW, IS THAT NICE?

16:13.340 --> 16:14.774
HERE I AM, ACTUALLY
GIVING YOU THE TIME OF DAY,

16:14.807 --> 16:15.575
AND ALL YOU CAN DO
IS LEVEL

16:15.608 --> 16:19.246
A RATHER PEDESTRIAN CURSE
AT ME.

16:19.279 --> 16:20.780
- HEY, BRIAN.
WAIT.

16:20.813 --> 16:26.619
COME HAVE A DRINK ON ME.

16:26.653 --> 16:28.688
A COUPLE OF DEWARS.

16:28.721 --> 16:31.724
- WELL, WE'RE SERIOUS TONIGHT.

16:31.758 --> 16:35.228
- THE UNTHINKABLE
HAS HAPPENED.

16:35.262 --> 16:37.497
- "TED SCHMIDT WOKE ONE MORNING
FROM FITFUL DREAMS

16:37.530 --> 16:38.765
"TO FIND HIMSELF TRANSFORMED

16:38.798 --> 16:41.234
IN HIS BED
INTO A GIANT VAGINA."

16:41.268 --> 16:43.570
- WORSE.

16:43.603 --> 16:46.573
I'M...

16:46.606 --> 16:49.109
IMMUNE.

16:49.142 --> 16:50.643
- TO PENICILLIN?

16:50.677 --> 16:52.379
TO CLEVER
LITERARY REFERENCES?

16:52.412 --> 16:55.348
- TO PORN.

16:55.382 --> 16:57.217
I LOOK AT IT,
AND IT HAS NO EFFECT ON ME.

16:57.250 --> 16:59.286
ZIPPO.
NADA.

16:59.319 --> 17:01.621
I TOTALLY LOST INTEREST
IN IT.

17:01.654 --> 17:04.091
AND I DIDN'T
EVEN KNOW IT.

17:04.124 --> 17:06.659
ONE DAY, SUDDENLY,
IT'S JUST GONE.

17:06.693 --> 17:08.661
- YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY.
TOO MUCH OF A GOOD THING--

17:08.695 --> 17:12.332
- YOU'RE NOT HELPING.

17:12.365 --> 17:15.435
I'VE SEEN ALL MY WILDEST
FANTASIES FULFILLED,

17:15.468 --> 17:17.470
LIVE AND UNCENSORED
RIGHT BEFORE MY EYES,

17:17.504 --> 17:20.607
OVER AND OVER...

17:20.640 --> 17:22.142
AND OVER.
- I GOT IT.

17:22.175 --> 17:23.643
- SO MAY--
MAYBE I NEED TO

17:23.676 --> 17:25.145
LAY OFF FOR A WHILE,
YOU KNOW,

17:25.178 --> 17:26.479
JUST GIVE IT A REST.

17:26.513 --> 17:29.782
- OR MAYBE YOU NEED
TO STOP WATCHING AND DO.

17:29.816 --> 17:32.185
- [scoffs]

17:32.219 --> 17:35.455
- WHAT'S
YOUR MOST SECRET SEXUAL FANTASY?

17:35.488 --> 17:37.424
- ARE YOU CRAZY?

17:37.457 --> 17:39.792
I'M NOT TELLING YOU THAT.
- FINE.

17:39.826 --> 17:41.661
LIVE OUT THE REMAINDER
OF YOUR DAYS

17:41.694 --> 17:44.097
CONDEMNED
TO SEXUAL PURGATORY.

17:44.131 --> 17:48.501
- ALL RIGHT.

17:48.535 --> 17:50.337
BUT IF I TELL YOU,
DO YOU PROMISE

17:50.370 --> 17:51.838
NOT TO MAKE ME FEEL
LIKE A FOOL?

17:51.871 --> 17:53.873
- THAT WOULD BE REDUNDANT.

17:53.906 --> 17:57.444
[techno music]

17:57.477 --> 18:03.850
*

18:03.883 --> 18:07.854
- [whispers indistinctly]

18:07.887 --> 18:09.456
*

18:09.489 --> 18:14.227
- I MAY HAVE SERIOUSLY
UNDERESTIMATED YOU, THEODORE.

18:15.528 --> 18:17.297
- THERE YOU GO, EM.

18:17.330 --> 18:21.468
COME ON.

18:21.501 --> 18:22.569
- LOOK, LOOK!

18:22.602 --> 18:24.404
I DID IT.
I GOT THEM ALL DOWN.

18:24.437 --> 18:26.406
[chuckles]
- THE NEXT TIME, HONEY,

18:26.439 --> 18:28.408
TRY AND DO IT IN YOUR LANE.

18:28.441 --> 18:30.777
[both chuckling]

18:30.810 --> 18:31.811
- GOTTA HAND IT
TO YOU, MOM,

18:31.844 --> 18:35.582
THIS MATCH IS THE WORST IDEA
YOU HAVE EVER HAD.

18:35.615 --> 18:37.650
- WELL, WHAT WAS
I SUPPOSED TO DO?

18:37.684 --> 18:39.919
LET THEM GET AWAY
WITH MAKING FUN OF GAY BOWLERS?

18:39.952 --> 18:41.821
- WE DO.
- YEAH, WELL, THEY'RE COPS.

18:41.854 --> 18:43.356
THEY SHOULD BE HELD
TO A HIGHER STANDARD.

18:43.390 --> 18:45.225
- RIGHT.
- WE'RE GOING TO DO FINE.

18:45.258 --> 18:48.395
- ALL WE NEED TO DO IS PRACTICE.
- THAT'S RIGHT.

18:48.428 --> 18:50.230
'CAUSE PRACTICE MAKES PERFECT.

18:50.263 --> 18:52.299
- BRIAN ALREADY IS PERFECT.

18:52.332 --> 18:54.234
- GLAD YOU THINK SO.

18:54.267 --> 18:55.668
- YEAH,
A LITTLE MORE PRACTICE,

18:55.702 --> 18:57.670
AND I'LL BE PERFECT TOO.

18:57.704 --> 18:59.539
- YOU ACTUALLY HAVE
A LOT OF POTENTIAL, EMMETT.

18:59.572 --> 19:00.540
- FOR MANSLAUGHTER.

19:00.573 --> 19:04.444
- YOU JUST NEED TO WORK
ON YOUR FOLLOW-THROUGH.

19:04.477 --> 19:06.579
SEE, WHEREVER YOUR HAND GOES,
THE BALL GOES.

19:06.613 --> 19:09.949
SO JUST PRETEND YOU'RE THROWING
RIGHT AT THE PINS.

19:09.982 --> 19:12.919
- THROW YOUR HAND
AT THE PINS.

19:19.459 --> 19:21.794
- WHOO!

19:21.828 --> 19:23.530
WELCOME TO TEAM HOMO!

19:23.563 --> 19:24.864
- WHAT?

19:24.897 --> 19:26.266
DEBBIE, YOU ALREADY HAVE
A FULL LINEUP.

19:26.299 --> 19:27.667
- YEAH, WELL...

19:27.700 --> 19:30.637
WE JUST LOST A PLAYER.

19:30.670 --> 19:33.540
EMMETT, YOU'RE OFF THE TEAM.

19:33.573 --> 19:34.607
- [chuckling]

19:34.641 --> 19:35.842
- WHAT EVER HAPPENED TO

19:35.875 --> 19:37.277
"IT'S NOT
WHETHER YOU WIN OR LOSE,

19:37.310 --> 19:38.711
IT'S HOW YOU PLAY THE GAME"?

19:38.745 --> 19:40.547
- WELL, IT NEEDS A REWRITE.

19:40.580 --> 19:41.548
- SORRY, MOM.

19:41.581 --> 19:43.616
HE JUST GOT OUT OF THE HOSPITAL.
IT'S TOO SOON.

19:43.650 --> 19:44.884
- MICHAEL,

19:44.917 --> 19:46.353
I'M FINE.
- AH, YEAH.

19:46.386 --> 19:48.521
AND I WOULD LIKE YOU
TO STAY THAT WAY.

19:48.555 --> 19:50.923
YOU SHOULDN'T BE DOING ANYTHING
PHYSICALLY STRENUOUS.

19:50.957 --> 19:52.359
- HEAR THAT, PROFESSOR?

19:52.392 --> 19:54.494
NO MORE HEAVY BUTT ACTION.

19:54.527 --> 19:56.629
- DO YOU MIND?
- JUST LOOKING AFTER HIS HEALTH.

19:56.663 --> 19:57.930
- FOR CHRIST'S SAKE,
MICHAEL.

19:57.964 --> 19:59.299
WOULD YOU STOP BEING
A MOTHER HEN?

19:59.332 --> 20:01.968
THAT'S MY JOB.
HE SAYS HE FEELS FINE.

20:02.001 --> 20:06.439
- HE'S NOT BOWLING,
AND THAT'S FINAL.

20:06.473 --> 20:09.242
- WELL,
I GUESS I'M ON THE TEAM,

20:09.276 --> 20:14.847
WHETHER HER MAJESTY
LIKES IT OR NOT.

20:14.881 --> 20:17.317
[overlapping chatter]

20:17.350 --> 20:20.853
- I'M FEELING GOOD ABOUT THIS.
YES, I AM.

20:20.887 --> 20:21.888
WE'RE GOOD.

20:21.921 --> 20:23.790
- LOOK WHO'S HERE.
- [chuckles]

20:23.823 --> 20:26.326
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU,
CHECKING OUT THE COMPETITION?

20:26.359 --> 20:28.328
- CHECKING IT OUT
REAL CLOSELY.

20:28.361 --> 20:30.297
I LIKE WHAT I SEE.
HEY, VIC.

20:30.330 --> 20:31.264
- HEY.
- [clears throat]

20:31.298 --> 20:32.599
- LEAVE IT TO MY SISTER
TO GET US INTO THIS.

20:32.632 --> 20:33.800
- MICHAEL,
COVER YOUR EYES.

20:33.833 --> 20:35.034
- GUESS WE MIGHT
AS WELL HAVE FUN.

20:35.067 --> 20:36.369
- HEY, YOU LOOK LIKE
YOU NEED A DRINK.

20:36.403 --> 20:38.004
- FOR ONCE,
WE CAN BE ALONE.

20:38.037 --> 20:41.874
- OH, WAIT A MINUTE.
MY KID'S STANDING RIGHT THERE.

20:41.908 --> 20:45.412
- I JUST WANNA GIVE YOU
A LITTLE KISS.

20:45.445 --> 20:47.480
HOW ABOUT WE GO OUT
FOR A DRINK?

20:47.514 --> 20:49.382
- I CAN'T, I'M MEETING
WITH THE GUYS.

20:49.416 --> 20:51.751
WE'RE STRATEGIZING
FOR THE GAME.

20:51.784 --> 20:53.620
[chuckles]
- AH.

20:53.653 --> 20:56.022
GO AHEAD,
I WON'T KEEP YOU.

20:56.055 --> 21:00.960
CONSIDERING WHAT AN EXPERT
YOU ARE AT GAMES.

21:00.993 --> 21:04.030
- PARDON?
- FORGET IT.

21:04.063 --> 21:05.898
- NO, YOU CAN'T JUST THROW
SOMETHING LIKE THAT OUT THERE

21:05.932 --> 21:07.767
AND SAY, "FORGET IT."
- I'M A DETECTIVE.

21:07.800 --> 21:08.901
I KNOW HOW TO READ PEOPLE.

21:08.935 --> 21:10.403
YOU'RE COMING THROUGH
LOUD AND CLEAR.

21:10.437 --> 21:13.706
- WELL, I WISH YOU WERE.

21:18.711 --> 21:21.481
- EVERY TIME I TRY TO GET
A LITTLE FRIENDLY,

21:21.514 --> 21:22.949
YOU SHOOT ME DOWN.

21:22.982 --> 21:25.452
- NO, I MEAN, I TOLD YOU.
IT'S JUST THAT--

21:25.485 --> 21:28.054
- YOU CAN'T DESERT
YOUR TEAM.

21:28.087 --> 21:29.889
IF IT WASN'T THIS,

21:29.922 --> 21:31.658
YOU'D BE STUFFING ENVELOPES
FOR PFLAG

21:31.691 --> 21:34.794
OR MARCHING FOR GAY RIGHTS

21:34.827 --> 21:37.063
OR SOME OTHER EXCUSE
NOT TO GET CLOSE.

21:37.096 --> 21:40.800
- THAT'S BULLSHIT.

21:40.833 --> 21:42.335
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW ME.

21:42.369 --> 21:45.638
- WHO DO WE HAVE TO THANK
FOR THAT?

21:50.843 --> 21:53.480
[car horn honks]

21:53.513 --> 21:56.583
- YOU'RE MAKING
TOO BIG A DEAL.

21:56.616 --> 21:59.819
- TOO BIG A DEAL--
YOU PRACTICALLY DIED.

21:59.852 --> 22:01.521
- YEAH, BUT I DIDN'T,
MICHAEL.

22:01.554 --> 22:04.023
I AM STILL HERE.

22:04.056 --> 22:06.125
- YEAH.

22:06.158 --> 22:08.361
AND I STILL WAKE UP
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT

22:08.395 --> 22:10.630
AND LISTEN
TO YOU BREATHE...

22:10.663 --> 22:13.500
JUST TO BE SURE.

22:13.533 --> 22:17.604
I DON'T WANT ANYTHING ELSE
TO HAPPEN TO YOU.

22:17.637 --> 22:19.439
- IF IT'S THAT IMPORTANT,

22:19.472 --> 22:21.408
YOU CAN BENCH MY ASS.

22:21.441 --> 22:23.676
NOW STOP WORRYING.

22:23.710 --> 22:25.978
- I CAN'T HELP IT.

22:26.012 --> 22:29.382
I HAVE THE GENES OF
AN ITALIAN MOTHER IN MY BLOOD.

22:29.416 --> 22:33.620
- MM.
SO HOW COME YOU CAN'T COOK?

22:33.653 --> 22:34.854
- I WORRY ABOUT EVERYBODY.

22:34.887 --> 22:36.456
I WORRY ABOUT VIC,

22:36.489 --> 22:38.591
I WORRY
ABOUT TED AND EMMETT,

22:38.625 --> 22:40.660
I WORRY
ABOUT BRIAN AND JUSTIN...

22:40.693 --> 22:42.729
- HMM.
WHAT IS THEIR PROBLEM?

22:42.762 --> 22:46.533
WHAT, WHICH HOT TRICK
THEY'RE GOING TO FUCK NEXT?

22:46.566 --> 22:50.036
- I SAW JUSTIN
KISSING SOME GUY.

22:50.069 --> 22:52.505
- MICHAEL, I KISS GUYS
ALL THE TIME.

22:52.539 --> 22:54.574
- YOU DO?

22:54.607 --> 22:55.875
- YEAH, I KISS THEM HELLO,

22:55.908 --> 22:56.943
I KISS THEM GOOD-BYE, I--

22:56.976 --> 22:58.578
- IT WASN'T THAT KIND
OF A KISS.

22:58.611 --> 22:59.746
- OH.

22:59.779 --> 23:01.814
MM.

23:08.755 --> 23:10.490
- IT WAS THAT KIND
OF A KISS.

23:10.523 --> 23:12.525
- [sighs]

23:15.061 --> 23:17.630
OKAY, UH--

23:17.664 --> 23:19.732
DOES, UH--

23:19.766 --> 23:22.802
DOES HE KNOW
THAT YOU SAW HIM?

23:22.835 --> 23:24.637
- I WAS ACROSS THE STREET.

23:24.671 --> 23:27.574
SO DO I TELL BRIAN OR NOT?

23:27.607 --> 23:29.609
- ABSOLUTELY NOT.

23:29.642 --> 23:31.678
- WHAT? RULE NUMBER
TWO OF GAY ETIQUETTE:

23:31.711 --> 23:33.513
NEVER TELL YOUR BEST FRIEND
THAT HIS BOYFRIEND

23:33.546 --> 23:34.681
IS CHEATING ON HIM?

23:34.714 --> 23:36.916
- IF YOU'RE WRONG,
HE WILL BE FURIOUS.

23:36.949 --> 23:38.050
- AND IF I'M RIGHT?

23:38.084 --> 23:40.920
- HE'LL BE EVEN FURIOUSER.

23:40.953 --> 23:43.790
- SO EITHER WAY I LOSE.

23:43.823 --> 23:45.758
[sighs]

23:45.792 --> 23:50.162
- YOU'RE NOT GOING TO LIE HERE
ALL NIGHT WORRYING.

23:50.196 --> 23:53.933
- I TOLD YOU,
IT'S GENETIC.

23:53.966 --> 23:55.535
[sighs]

23:55.568 --> 23:58.538
[electronic music]

23:58.571 --> 24:06.579
*

24:34.040 --> 24:36.876
- [sniffs]

25:10.276 --> 25:11.644
IT WAS INCREDIBLE!

25:11.678 --> 25:13.179
- THE BOYS
BEHAVED THEMSELVES?

25:13.212 --> 25:15.615
- "MISBEHAVED"
IS MORE LIKE IT.

25:15.648 --> 25:16.616
IT WAS JUST
WHAT I NEEDED.

25:16.649 --> 25:18.751
I REALLY GOT
MY GROOVE BACK.

25:18.785 --> 25:19.986
- GROOVY.

25:20.019 --> 25:22.555
- HOW CAN I EVER
THANK YOU?

25:22.589 --> 25:24.757
- YOU CAN'T.

25:24.791 --> 25:26.325
HEY, WHAT SIZE
DOES THIS COME IN?

25:26.358 --> 25:30.262
- TWINK, STUD,
AND BEAR.

25:30.296 --> 25:31.864
- I'LL TAKE A STUD.

25:31.898 --> 25:33.032
- I'LL TAKE TWO.

25:33.065 --> 25:34.066
- [chuckles]

25:34.100 --> 25:35.868
- [chuckles]

25:35.902 --> 25:37.837
- BY THE WAY,
AREN'T YOU FORGETTING SOMETHING?

25:37.870 --> 25:40.673
- OH. RIGHT.
[chuckling]

25:46.212 --> 25:47.279
[chuckles]

25:47.313 --> 25:49.949
OH.
[chuckles]

25:53.986 --> 25:56.956
[door closes]

25:56.989 --> 25:59.058
- SO WHAT WAS THAT
ALL ABOUT?

25:59.091 --> 26:01.060
AND WHAT WERE YOU DOING
WITH BRIAN'S BRACELET?

26:01.093 --> 26:02.895
- NEVER MIND.

26:02.929 --> 26:05.131
- TEDDY.

26:05.164 --> 26:06.933
SINCE WHEN
DO WE KEEP SECRETS?

26:06.966 --> 26:08.367
AND SINCE WHEN DO WE
SHARE THINGS WITH BRIAN

26:08.400 --> 26:11.570
THAT WE DO NOT SHARE
WITH ME?

26:16.709 --> 26:19.178
- I BORROWED IT.

26:19.211 --> 26:21.948
BRIEFLY.

26:21.981 --> 26:24.350
ALONG WITH HIS LIFE.

26:24.383 --> 26:25.652
I JUST WANTED TO SEE
WHAT IT WAS LIKE

26:25.685 --> 26:27.219
TO BE HIM.

26:27.253 --> 26:29.221
- DISH.

26:31.157 --> 26:34.126
[electronic music]

26:34.160 --> 26:38.631
*

26:38.665 --> 26:40.967
- [sputters and spits]

26:41.000 --> 26:42.368
[sniffs]

26:42.401 --> 26:44.103
OH, OH.

26:44.136 --> 26:46.973
FUCK.
[snorts out air]

26:47.006 --> 26:49.275
HEY, UH--
HI.

26:49.308 --> 26:50.910
I CAN GET IN?

26:50.943 --> 26:54.113
[grunts]

26:54.146 --> 26:55.882
OH, SORRY.

26:55.915 --> 26:57.784
THAT'S NOT--

26:57.817 --> 27:00.252
YOU GUYS ARE SLIPPERY.

27:00.286 --> 27:02.054
IT WAS AWFUL.

27:02.088 --> 27:04.356
EMPTY, MEANINGLESS.

27:04.390 --> 27:07.894
- WOW, YOU REALLY
WERE BRIAN.

27:07.927 --> 27:11.130
- MY ALL-TIME
NUMBER ONE FANTASY.

27:11.163 --> 27:15.101
NOW THAT'S GONE,
WHAT DO I HAVE LEFT?

27:15.134 --> 27:17.870
- HERE.
TRY THIS ON.

27:17.904 --> 27:19.906
- [sighs]

27:19.939 --> 27:22.709
- AFTER A WHILE,
DREAMS WEAR THIN.

27:22.742 --> 27:25.144
KIND OF LIKE THIS FABRIC.

27:25.177 --> 27:29.015
THEN, YOU REALIZE
YOU NEED SOMETHING MORE.

27:29.048 --> 27:31.217
- I WAS HOPING TO FIND
THAT WITH LUKE.

27:31.250 --> 27:32.351
- YEAH.

27:32.384 --> 27:34.153
HE WAS A SWEET BOY.

27:34.186 --> 27:36.923
BUT HE COULDN'T ACCEPT YOU
FOR WHO YOU ARE.

27:36.956 --> 27:40.659
TURN AROUND.

27:43.162 --> 27:45.231
YOU'LL FIND IT
WITH SOMEONE ELSE.

27:45.264 --> 27:46.833
- YEAH, RIGHT.

27:46.866 --> 27:49.235
- LOVE COMES
AT THE STRANGEST TIME

27:49.268 --> 27:52.038
IN THE STRANGEST WAYS.

27:52.071 --> 27:53.940
IT'LL HAPPEN FOR YOU.

27:53.973 --> 27:56.943
JUST YOU WAIT AND SEE.

27:58.377 --> 28:02.014
MM, YOU ARE ONE HANDSOME DEVIL,
TED SCHMIDT.

28:02.048 --> 28:04.083
YOU KNOW THAT?

28:10.957 --> 28:13.392
- READY?

28:13.425 --> 28:16.195
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

28:16.228 --> 28:19.465
- OH, MY GOD.

28:19.498 --> 28:22.835
- IT'S GORGEOUS.

28:22.869 --> 28:27.740
